oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Martha White Grand Ole Opry - 1966-01-29
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The recording is of a variety of live shows from the Grand Ole Opry. The shows include multiple sponsors including: Martha White and Sephen's Work Clothes. The recordings feature artist performances by: the Osborne Brothers (musical group), Connie Smith (musician), Grandpa Jones (musician), the Crook Brothers (musical group), the Wilburn Brothers (musicial group), Roy Acuff (musician), Norma Jean (musician), Cousin Jody (musician), Ernest Tubb (musician) and Jean Shepard (musician). The Martha White show is from January 29, 1966. The remaining recordings are from a group of unidentified dates. The tape is labeled the fourth of thirteen.
